               <head>Commentary on books III-IV of Rumi’s Masnavi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Muḥammad ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Quṭb al-Dīn</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1043B-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7329">Muḥammad ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Quṭb al-Dīn</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7329">محمّد عبد العلى ابن قطب الدّين </persName>
                     </author>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled commentary on daftars III-IV of the <title>Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title> of Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī (d. 670/1271) by Mawlānā Muḥammad ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Quṭb al-Dīn, composed circa 1700. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon to daftar IV (f. 237v): completed by <persName key="person_f7202" role="scr">Jīvan Bayg ibn ʿĀshūr Bayg ibn Rashīd Bayg</persName> at <placeName>Shāhjahānābād</placeName>, midday Friday, 10 Jumādá I 1250/14 September 1834, Christian Era stated as <sic>1835</sic>, in the reign of Emperor Akbar [II]. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Rough nastaʿlīq on burnished English (?) laid paper with manufacturer’s watermarks. 
</p>
                        <p>Occasional annotations and corrections in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped and Persian foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding. Current decaying leather binding postdates 1862. </p>
                        <p>Folios bound; damp and fungal damage; ink smudged or transferred in parts. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
